<TITLE> DCC commissioner gets 10 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka City Corporation commissioner was sentenced to 10 years in jail Wednesday in a Tk 20 lakh extortion case. The verdict was handed down to DCC commissioner Chowdhury Alam (ward No. 56) by Dhaka metropolitan assistant sessions judge Md Shafiul Azam. He was also fined Tk 50,000 or further one year's rigorous imprisonment on failure to pay. Three others accused in the caseDelwar Hossain Ripon, Harunur Rashid and Rezaul Talukderwere cleared of the charges. According to the case proceedings, on August 20, 2003, Chowdhury Alam demanded Tk 20 lakh from Babul Miah, owner of Bangladesh Super Market at Fulbaria in the capital. Chowdhury Alam and his accomplices went to Babul Miah's office to collect the money on August 30 of the same year. Babul Miah's wife Aleya Babul filed a case on May 7 this year with Shahbagh Police Station, accusing 25 people in connection with the incident. The investigation officer of the case, sub-inspector Rabiul Haque, pressed charges against four persons in the case on June 18. After investigations, the police dropped 21 people from the chargesheet. Chowdhury Alam surrendered to the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court on Feb 22. He was sent to jail the same day. bdnews
